In our detailed Benchmark analyses of PFAS immunotoxicity we examined a variety of dose-response models in two different data sets with several outcome variables. It is clearly challenging to derive a reference dose level based on multiple BMDLs. Still, EFSA has provided guidelines of how to proceed in this situation [ 3 ,  4 ,  16 ]. At the time of this calculation, the recommended procedure was roughly speaking: for each outcome, results from all models that fit almost as a as well as the best fitting model is retained ( \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
